developed typhoon status churning up winds of 75 mph 
ofelia had been expected to cross the northern tip of luzon the 
main philippine island but officials said the storm veered 
northward skimming the east coast of luzons cagayan province 
before heading toward batanes the northernmost philippine 
province about 400 miles north of manila 
it was the second big storm to strike the country this eyear 
storm warnings were raised over 13 luzon provinces and small 
craft were warned to remain in port residents of the affected 
provinces were warned to be alert for landslides and flooding 
in manila heavy rains drenched the city throughout the night 
and waves crashed over the seawall along manila bay schools were 
closed today and widespread areas of the city were without 
electricity 
