in white aprons pulling dustcovered bodies from under concrete 
slabs the corpses were laid on blocks of ice in open trucks 
apparently to keep them from decomposing 
a dam south of rasht burst flooding the surrounding area irna 
said 
frightened survivors spent the night outdoors afraid to go 
home in quakedevastated towns women in black chadors flanked by 
weeping children camped out in public squares 
