<TEXT>
the highly publicized suicide of a member of 
the unitarian church focused new attention on the denominations 
liberal social stands as leaders began their annual conference 
friday 
two years ago the church endorsed the right to die and leaders 
voiced support for janet adkins an alzheimers disease patient who 
used a suicide machine to end her life june 4 
the issue was expected to be a prime topic of discussion at the 
