orlando in 1971 
she also was convicted of killing her paralyzed son michael 
goodyear 19 by pushing him from a canoe in a 1980 outing and of 
attempted murder in a car bombing that injured her boyfriend john 
gentry in 1983 
she would be the second woman executed in the united states 
since the us supreme court lifted its ban on capital punishment 
in 1976 north carolina killed velma barfield by lethal injection 
