<TEXT>
the capital of iran jammed with poor 
peasants hunting jobs that arent there has become a morass of 
poverty and pollution 
its population has doubled to 8 million since the islamic 
revolution of 1979 swollen by a birth rate of 35 percent a year 
and migration from the countryside that is about oneseventh of 
the national population 55 million 
tehran and other overpopulated cities have expanded so much 
that a remedy has to be found the daily newspaper abrar 
declared the problems are so complex that it seems even the most 
skilled planners are at a loss to find a workable program 
beyond the 8 million officially counted tehran has a floating 
