the administration and the sec said the measure is necessary to 
prevent sharp rises and drops in market prices the futures 
industry and the cftc strongly oppose the bill 
the proposal also would give the sec authority to oversee stock 
index futures margins the downpayment required of investors who 
buy the contracts on credit 
the futures exchanges currently set those margins which are 
generally much lower than those of securities the sec and treasury 
have said low margins on stock index futures were partly to blame 
for the 1987 stock market crash and the 190point drop last october 
stock index futures allow investors to speculate on movements in 
the stock market without buying the underlying stocks 
the administration proposal was introduced as a separate bill in 
the house but will be included in cftc market reform legislation 
