you have to take them into account said steve lampe of rd 
smith 
the agreement calls for ames to pay 78 million in vacation pay 
to the 18000 workers and 165 million in severance pay it also 
calls for ames to pay 850000 in vacation pay to the 6600 
employees laid off just before the bankruptcy filing 
the company employed about 55000 people before the filing 
