fears 
technology has been one of the major reasons for the success 
in american agriculture said john urbanchek a senior vice 
president for economics in the washington office of the consulting 
firm hill and knowlton inc 
the problem is that the contribution of current technology is 
being rapidly exhausted and must be replaced if the us is to 
retain its prominence as an agricultural producer and exporter and 
to continue to supply american consumers with highquality safe 
and reasonably priced food he said 
