a federal appeals court today reinstated a 
potential multibilliondollar lawsuit by the states of california 
arizona oregon and washington that accuses oil companies of 
conspiring to fix prices and contrive a gasoline shortage in the 
early 1970s 
the suit against seven major companies was dismissed in 1986 by 
us district judge william gray of los angeles who said the 
states had failed to present evidence of a conspiracy in violation 
of antitrust laws 
but the 9th us circuit court of appeals in a 30 decision 
said today that evidence of information exchanges and parallel 
actions by the companies would allow a jury to find that a 
conspiracy existed 
the ruling if it stands would send the case to trial robert 
mittelstaedt a lawyer for chevron corp said no decision had been 
reached yet on whether to appeal 
