<TEXT>
minneapolisbased first bank systems 
inc on thursday terminated its planned acquisition of banks of 
iowa inc iowas biggest bank holding company breaking off an 
8year engagement 
the courtship of des moinesbased banks of iowa by first bank 
had been at the center of an acrimonious debate over legalizing 
interstate banking in iowa iowas interstate banking law becomes 
effective in 1991 
but holmes foster chairman of banks of iowa told shareholders 
at the companys annual meeting that the deal fell through because 
a weakened financial condition left first bank system unable to 
obtain the necessary regulatory approval for the takeover 
