minnesota authorized such deals in 1986 this year after years 
of bitter legislative battles iowa passed an interstate banking 
law that will take effect at the beginning of 1991 the iowa law 
allows interstate banking with institutions in adjoining states 
but before the deal became legal first bank system ran into 
financial difficulties 
