the administration and the sec said the index futures measure is 
necessary to best regulate the securities which some critics hold 
responsible for sharp rises and drops in market prices 
the proposal also would give the sec authority to oversee stock 
index futures margins the down payment required of investors who 
buy the securities on credit 
the commodity futures exchanges currently set those margins 
which are generally much lower than those for securities the sec 
and treasury have said low stock index futures margins partly were 
to blame for the 1987 stock market crash and the 190point market 
drop last october 
stock index futures allow investors to speculate on movements in 
the stock market without buying the underlying stock 
the administration proposal strongly opposed by the futures 
industry and the cftc was introduced as a separate bill in the 
house but will be included in cftc market reform legislation which 
has been pending since last fall 
