<TEXT>
shamrock holdings the private investment 
company headed by walt disneys nephew roy disney has formed a 
partnership to bail out companies overburdened by debt shamrocks 
chief strategist said friday 
the 450 million fund raised money primarily from previous 
investors in shamrock the company that last year failed to acquire 
polaroid corp after a long highly publicized bid 
several such funds have emerged recently with the intent of 
rescuing companies that overleveraged themselves during the 
borrowing frenzy of the 1980s 
its all youre going to be seeing for the next two years 
shamrocks chief executive stanley p gold said in a telephone 
interview 
shamrocks fund trefoil capital partners is allowed to attempt 
hostile takeovers under the terms of the partnership however it 
is expected to concentrate on friendly white knight deals 
shamrock takes a 1 percent fee for managing the partnership 
a white knight is a third party that often acquires a stake in a 
company to help a takeover target avoid an unfriendly merger 
we want to do three or four deals gold said about 150 
million to 250 million is the ideal 
the partnership already has offered to provide capital for 
struggling companies including southland corp and ames department 
stores both filed for protection from creditors in us bankruptcy 
court 
shamrock also was interested in investing in koor inc israels 
biggest conglomerate which is struggling to service a 12 billion 
debt that offer basically a restructuring in which creditors 
would forgive some koor debt is typical of those trefoil will 
make gold said 
trefoil said it would buy a stake in koor with 100 million of 
new equity if the banks and bondholders would forgive half of their 
12 billion in koor debt no deal has been worked out yet 
theyre trying to restructure their debt gold said they 
may come back to us after they make some progress 
at a time when junk bond and bank financing for big investors is 
hard to come by the fund will provide shamrock with a ready source 
of funds so it can move fast if it spots an attractive deal 
gold said the partnership expects to complete its first deal by 
the end of the year 
shamrock owns the music plus music and video stores in southern 
california and the sound warehouse chain in texas it also owns 15 
radio and three television stations 15 percent of oil field 
equipment maker enterra corp and has various real estate holdings 
trefoil is looking into deals in similar industries officials 
said 
